      • value

        public SymmetricEncryptionAttribute.EncryptionSpecs value()
        Simply return the value of encryptionSpecs Note that returning a reference to an object held inside the attribute implementation means that external users can modify inside the implementation; to avoid this, attribute implementations should return new instances of the returned value, e.g. return new String(value). Alternatively, implementations can implement a form of cloning in order to protect the original reference. Most applications, however, will likely return the (new) result of some calculation and this should not be an issue.
